<h1>About Dog Breed Explorer</h1>

<h2>Description</h2>

<p>
  Dog Breed Explorer is a Ruby on Rails application that displays
  dog breeds, sub-breeds, and dog images. Users can browse the breed
  collection and view more information about each breed.
</p>

<h2>Data Source</h2>

<p>
  The main data source for this project is the Dog CEO API.
  The API provides dog breed names, sub-breed names, and image URLs
  in JSON format.
</p>

<p>
  Faker is used to generate simple descriptions. The dog breed names,
  sub-breed names, and image URLs all come from the Dog CEO API.
</p>

<h2>Database Structure</h2>

<p>
  The application uses three database tables: breeds, sub_breeds,
  and dog_images. One breed can have many sub-breeds and many dog images.
</p>